    "While in the previous section we show that words associated with the commercial potential class are mostly scientific or technical in nature, we do find that certain words are more generic.",
    "However, this analysis does not fully address whether commercially oriented words are influencing the results.",
    "One the one hand, to classify an abstract, our methodology employs transformers, which consider combinations of words and their semantic meaning within a document, rather than individual words alone.",
    "On the other, it is also possible that these words appear only in abstracts that are indeed commercially promising, particularly since these are abstracts of papers published in peer-reviewed journals and that, thus, are potentially tuned down."
  ]
